# Testing

- **Framework:** Vitest + React Testing Library.
- **Location:** Sibling colocation only — `Feature.tsx` + `Feature.test.tsx` in the same folder. No `__tests__/` folders, no `src/test/` or `src/tests/`. Shared harness is repo-root `vitest/` (`@vitest-harness/*`).
- **Philosophy:** Test behavior, not implementation details.
- **Mocking:** Mock Supabase client calls and Service layer functions. Do not mock internal component state logic if possible.
- **Selectors:** Use accessible selectors (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`) over `getByTestId` when possible.

## Performance (#1314)

- Prefer **unit** (`.test.ts` / node project) for pure utils; reserve `.test.tsx` (jsdom) for UI behavior.
- Shared wrappers (`TestProviders`, `JourneyProviders`) must stabilize `QueryClient` with `useState(() => createTestQueryClient())` — never allocate a new client on every render.
- Prefer `getBy*` / `getAllBy*` when data is sync-mocked; reserve `findBy*` / `waitFor` for real async (portals, promises, mutations).
- Prefer `fireEvent` for simple clicks; use `userEvent` when testing keyboard/a11y sequencing.
- When `userEvent` is required (Radix Tabs/Select/DropdownMenu), call `userEvent.setup({ delay: null })` — default typing delay inflates suite times.
- Stub heavy children (calendars, checkbox pickers, column managers, nested Selects) when the suite under test only needs wiring; keep one focused suite with the real Radix/UI control.
- When product mounts CSS layout twins (desktop + mobile), mock the unused twin unless the test specifically covers both.
- Target: most new component tests under ~150–200ms when feasible.
- **Duration triage (#1349):** CI uploads per-shard JSON under `artifacts/vitest-results/`. The **Vitest Duration Report** job writes a GitHub Actions summary and a sticky PR comment (tests ≥200ms). Locally:

      gh run download <runId> -n vitest-results-shard-1 -n vitest-results-shard-2 -n vitest-results-shard-3 -n vitest-results-shard-4 -D tmp/vitest-perf/ci-<runId>
      npm run test:perf:report -- tmp/vitest-perf/ci-<runId>
      node scripts/vitest-perf/report-vitest-durations.mjs --markdown tmp/vitest-perf/ci-<runId>

  Report writes `tmp/vitest-perf/latest-report.txt`, `.md`, and `.json`. (Put path before flags when using `npm run`, or call `node` directly — npm can swallow `--markdown`.)
